  "text": "RADX levels must be carefully controlled as overexpression of RADX also increases DNA damage due to enhanced nascent strand degradation at stalled replication forks. This may be the result of RADX antagonizing the RAD51 filament formation and fork reversal. Reciprocally, depletion of RADX and the concomitant increase in RAD51 at the stalled fork rescues nascent strand degradation, but not HDR, in BRCA2-deficient cells. Interestingly, RADX depletion also restores fork protection in cells deficient for BODL1 [CITATION_1] . RAD51 nucleofilament formation in the absence of RADX may be significant enough to protect the regressed replication forks even in the absence of BRCA2 and BODL1 [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] .",
